            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ESatan%20is%20a%20master%20at%20setting%20traps%20for%20believers.%20He%20is%20called%20the%20%22fowler%22%20in%20Psalm%20124%3A7%20(KJV)%2C%20that%20is%2C%20a%20person%20who%20traps%20birds.%20Perhaps%20as%20a%20child%20you%20watched%20someone%20take%20bread%20crumbs%20and%20make%20a%20trail%20that%20led%20inside%20a%20box.%20The%20box%20was%20propped%20up%20on%20a%20stick%2C%20and%20a%20string%20was%20tied%20to%20the%20stick.%20The%20fowler%20waited%20behind%20a%20fence%20or%20a%20building%20while%20an%20unsuspecting%20bird%20followed%20the%20bread%20crumbs%20into%20the%20box.%20Then%2C%20at%20just%20the%20right%20moment%2C%20the%20fowler%20pulled%20the%20string%2C%20and%20the%20bird%20was%20caught.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDo%20you%20know%20someone%20who%20is%20following%20%22bread%20crumbs%22%20right%20now%3F%20Little%20enticements%20toward%20money%2C%20sex%2C%20addictions%2C%20or%20positions%20come%20at%20just%20the%20right%20time%20to%20keep%20the%20person%20moving%20toward%20the%20%22box.%22%20Satan%20knows%20that%20if%20he%20can%20get%20someone%20who%20has%20no%20accountability%20to%20others%20to%20move%20down%20a%20sinful%20path%2C%20he%20can%20ultimately%20%22pull%20the%20string%2C%22%20and%20the%20unsuspecting%20person%20will%20be%20trapped.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPublic%20embarrassment%2C%20loss%20of%20influence%2C%20and%20ultimately%20eternal%20death%20are%20Satan's%20intentions%20as%20the%20fowler.%20By%20God's%20grace%2C%20however%2C%20%22we%20escaped%20like%20a%20bird%20from%20a%20hunter's%20trap.%20The%20trap%20is%20broken%2C%20and%20we%20are%20free!%22%20(Psalm%20124%3A7).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
